A mobile device that is configured for wireless communi-
cation may be configured to operate as a remote control
device in a lighting control system, controlling one or more
lighting control devices of the lighting control system. The
remote control device may control the light intensity in a
space, for instance at a location of the remote control device,
in response to an ambient light intensity measured at the
remote control device. The remote control device may define
a user interface for receiving an input that indicates a desired
light intensity at the cation. The remote control device may
measure the ambient light intensity at the location via a light
detector, compare the measured ambient light intensity to
the desired light intensity, and cause the one or more lighting
control devices to adjust the ambient light intensity at the
remote control device until it agrees with the desired light
intensity.
